THE House of Representatives, on Thursday, ordered the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control to track and test the Chief Executive Officer of Multichoice, John Ugbe, for COVID-19. The lawmaker representing the Peoples Democratic Party (Akwa Ibom), Idem Unyime, who also heads the House Committee on Digital Satellite Television, Pay as You Go Tarrif Hike, issued this directive on behalf of the legislators. The lawmakers said they were acting in the interest of Nigerians. Details later. 